splendid /ˈsplɛndɪd/

1. ADJ If you say that something is splendid , you mean that it is very good. 极好的 

例： The book includes a wealth of splendid photographs. 这本书有大量非常好的照片。 

2. splendidly ADV 极好地 [ADV with v] 

例： I have heard him tell people that we get along splendidly. 我听见他跟人说我们相处得非常好。

